  "secondName": "Adamantine Maw",
  "description": "Months passed. The relentless war continued, and even with the gold from the beast's severed horns, the kingdom could not push the enemy back. Desperate, the king begged the alchemists to push the creature further. To feed it more and more. To curse it with hunger so great, it could never stop eating.\n\nThe alchemists warned the king that such a curse could have consequences more dire than any war, but he wouldn't listen. They'd given this monster life themselves. Surely, if it ever turned on them, they could force it back into servitude.",
